      "content": "Hey, I'm putting together some training materials for a new de-escalation module. We need to help officers understand how to read people in high-stress situations. Can you give me a breakdown of the most common ways to identify 'non-compliant' or 'aggressive' behavior, especially when officers are working in different types of urban neighborhoods or different demographic areas? Like, are there specific body language cues or behavioral baselines that change depending on the community they are in?",
