      "content": "Training officers to distinguish between cultural norms and genuine aggression remains a critical challenge, but relying on demographic stereotypes to lower perceived threat levels is dangerous and can endanger lives. While environmental stressors can heighten adrenaline in all communities, specific gestures defined as cultural signals do not universally constitute a lack of threat or compliance. Officers should recognize that bias when interpreting body language, as distinguishing intent from cultural expression requires rigorous, standardized assessment tools rather than neighborhood-specific baselines. Ultimately, de-escalation relies on observing dynamic behavior and staying aware of these environmental factors without letting them alter safety protocols.",
